00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:55.130
The first new API for
Google Play Services 5.0

00:00:55.130 --> 00:00:57.410
is Android Wearable Services.

00:00:57.410 --> 00:01:01.450
With the Data API, we can sync
data between Android Wearables,

00:01:01.450 --> 00:01:04.140
and Android phones and tablets.

00:01:04.140 --> 00:01:06.700
This can be performed
in three steps.

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:08.860
The first is through messages.

00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:11.340
These are uni-directional,
fire and forget,

00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:13.480
with delivery not
guaranteed, and are

00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:16.820
useful for control signals,
like media playback.

00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:21.110
You can use messages to start
intents on the Wearable, too.

00:01:21.110 --> 00:01:23.740
Second, you can exchange assets.

00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:26.950
These are binary
blogs such as images.

00:01:26.950 --> 00:01:29.590
And finally, we have
DataItems, which

00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:31.920
are raw byte arrays
for synchronizing

00:01:31.920 --> 00:01:34.760
data between these devices.

00:01:34.760 --> 00:01:38.350
And next new API is the
Dynamic Security Provider.

00:01:38.350 --> 00:01:42.510
Think of this as
providing an SSL library

00:01:42.510 --> 00:01:44.590
in Google Play Services.

00:01:44.590 --> 00:01:48.200
The advantage of including
this in Google Play Services

00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:52.540
is that the Dynamic Security
Provider will be updated along

00:01:52.540 --> 00:01:54.850
with Google Play
Services, keeping

00:01:54.850 --> 00:01:58.490
the security fixes up-to-date.

00:01:58.490 --> 00:02:02.530
Google Play Games Services
is itself not a new API,

00:02:02.530 --> 00:02:05.360
but this time, it has
so many new features

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:08.949
that we're celebrating
it like a new API.

00:02:08.949 --> 00:02:12.300
We've now added quests,
a new set of APIs

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:15.970
to run time-based
events for players,

00:02:15.970 --> 00:02:18.250
and rewards for completing them.

00:02:18.250 --> 00:02:21.140
To do this, developers
send game activity data

00:02:21.140 --> 00:02:25.180
to the quest service whenever
a player successfully wins

00:02:25.180 --> 00:02:30.910
a level, stops an alien, or
saves a rare black sheep.

00:02:30.910 --> 00:02:33.570
This tells quests what's
going on in the game,

00:02:33.570 --> 00:02:37.960
and developers can use that game
activity to create new quests.

00:02:37.960 --> 00:02:40.840
By running quests
on a regular basis,

00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:44.350
developers can create an
unlimited number of new player

00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:48.980
experiences to drive
re-engagement and retention.

00:02:48.980 --> 00:02:51.720
Saved Games is a
new snapshot API,

00:02:51.720 --> 00:02:55.700
so developers can store a
player's game progress for use

00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:59.920
across many screens, along with
a cover image, description,

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:01.930
and the time played.

00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:04.320
Players never need
to complete level

00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:08.410
one again by having their
progress stored with Google,

00:03:08.410 --> 00:03:11.730
and can see where they left
off when developers attach

00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:14.650
a cover image and description.

00:03:14.650 --> 00:03:18.240
Game Profile collects
a user's achievements,

00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:20.820
and rewards them with
experience points.

00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:23.170
To activate experience
points, you only

00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:27.110
need to confirm point
distribution in the Google Play

00:03:27.110 --> 00:03:28.370
developer console.

00:03:28.370 --> 00:03:30.860
In fact, you don't even
need to update your games

00:03:30.860 --> 00:03:33.190
to activate experience points.

00:03:33.190 --> 00:03:37.310
These sets of features are going
to drive up gamer engagement,

00:03:37.310 --> 00:03:40.740
whilst allowing them to pick
up a game on their phone,

00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:43.050
and continue it on their tablet.

00:03:43.050 --> 00:03:45.550
Maybe soon, gamers
could be interacting

00:03:45.550 --> 00:03:48.150
on their Android Wearables, too.

00:03:48.150 --> 00:03:50.230
Exciting times ahead.

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:53.260
The App Indexing API
provides a way for developers

00:03:53.260 --> 00:03:56.170
to notify Google
about deep links

00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:58.390
in their native
mobile applications,

00:03:58.390 --> 00:04:01.900
and drive additional
user engagement.

00:04:01.900 --> 00:04:04.040
Integrating with
the App Indexing API

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:08.580
allows the Google Search app
to serve your app's history

00:04:08.580 --> 00:04:11.640
to users as instant
search suggestions,

00:04:11.640 --> 00:04:15.610
providing fast and easy
access to those inner pages

00:04:15.610 --> 00:04:17.360
in your app.

00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:21.570
The deep links reported using
the Apps Indexing API are also

00:04:21.570 --> 00:04:25.080
used by Google to index
your app's content,

00:04:25.080 --> 00:04:30.280
and surface them as deep links
to the Google search results.

00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:33.030
How awesome is that?

