00:05:42.920 --> 00:05:47.470
When a user clicks the
Save card to Google button,

00:05:47.470 --> 00:05:49.840
the offer gets
saved, and shows up

00:05:49.840 --> 00:05:51.970
in the user's Google Wallet app.

00:05:51.970 --> 00:05:53.770
And here's the best part.

00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:56.830
Geo-fenced in-store
notifications

00:05:56.830 --> 00:06:00.960
prompt the user to show
and scan digital cards

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:05.800
at point-of-sales terminals,
driving higher redemption.

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:07.940
This also frees the
user from having

00:06:07.940 --> 00:06:11.230
to carry around offers
and loyalty cards,

00:06:11.230 --> 00:06:14.480
and provides a great
purchasing experience.

00:06:14.480 --> 00:06:17.540
In fact, merchants are
happier because they

00:06:17.540 --> 00:06:20.220
